description: International scientific vocabulary, from New Latin, from tubo- +‎ ligamentous = tubo- +‎ ligament +‎ -ous.

adjectives.description: tuboligamentous (comparative more tuboligamentous, superlative most tuboligamentous)

entries.meaning: (anatomy, medicine, surgery) Of or pertaining to both a tube and a ligament, and more specifically, the fallopian tube and the broad ligament.
